Indonesia Stocks: Aneka Tambang, Astra, Indocement, Indomobil

-- B y   B e r n i   M o e s t a f a
-- 
2011-05-11T09:24:06Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-11/indonesia-stocks-aneka-tambang-indocement-tunggal-indomobil.html
Shares of the following companies had
unusual moves in Indonesian trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are as of the 4 p.m. Jakarta-time close.  The  Jakarta Composite index (JCI)  advanced 37.62 points, or 1
percent, to 3,838.14, the steepest increase since April 20.  PT Aneka Tambang (ANTM IJ), the nation’s second-largest
nickel producer, rose 2.3 percent to 2,250 rupiah, on course for
the biggest increase since March 24. Nickel for three-month
delivery climbed 2 percent to $24,850 a metric ton in  London 
yesterday, the biggest gain since April 20.  PT Astra International (ASII IJ),  Indonesia ’s biggest
automotive retailer, jumped 4 percent to 59,250 rupiah, the most
since Jan. 25.  Standard & Poor’s  assigned the company with a
BBB- long-term corporate  credit rating  with a stable outlook.  PT Indocement Tunggal Prakarsa (INTP IJ), the nation’s
second-largest cement maker, rose 1.8 percent to 17,000 rupiah,
providing the biggest boost to the Jakarta Basic Industry and
Chemicals Index. Indocement said it will pay a total dividend of
263 rupiah a share.  PT Indomobil Sukses Internasional (IMAS IJ), an automotive
retailer, advanced 4.1 percent to 8,850 rupiah, the highest
close since April 26. The company said it plans to raise as much
as 3.28 trillion rupiah ($384 million) selling new shares in a
rights offer in July to pay debt and to expand its business.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Berni Moestafa in Jakarta at 
 bmoestafa@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Darren Boey at   dboey@bloomberg.net  